  大约20年前，当我写《因果关系》（Causality/2000）这本书的前言时，我做了一个相当大胆的评论，朋友建议我降低音调
  （i made a rather daring remark that friends advised me to tone down），“因果关系经历了重大转变(causality
  has undergone a major transformation)，”我写到，“从一个笼罩在神秘中的概念变成一个数学上具有良好定义和有根据
  的逻辑的对象”（“from a concept shrouded in mystery into a mathematical 
  object with well-ddefinedsemantics and well-founded logic.”）。
  矛盾和争议已经解决，(paradoxes and controversies have been resolved),
  滑动/模糊的概念已被阐明（slippery concepts have been explicated）,
  并且那些长期以来被视为形而上学或无法处理的、依赖因果信息的实际问题，现在可以用初级数学
  解决（and practical problems relying on causal information that long were regarded as 
  either metaphysical or unmanangeable
  can now be solved using elementary mathematics）。
  简而言之，因果关系一直是数学上的(Put simply,causality has been mathematizad)。
